{"image_id": "NEE_2013_page_106", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "NEXTERA ENERGY, INC. AND FLORIDA POWER & LIGHT COMPANY", "bbox": [299.9, 47.3, 975.4, 70.6]}, {"text": "NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS (Continued)", "bbox": [306.9, 72.3, 968.1, 95.6]}, {"text": "100", "bbox": [621.8, 1562.3, 653.0, 1583.2]}, {"text": "All price, volatility, correlation and customer migration inputs used in valuation are subject to validation by the Trading Risk", "bbox": [103.1, 127.9, 1177.1, 148.9]}, {"text": "Management group.  The Trading Risk Management group performs a risk management function responsible for assessing credit,", "bbox": [103.1, 150.4, 1177.1, 171.4]}, {"text": "market and operational risk impact, reviewing valuation methodology and modeling, confirming transactions, monitoring approval", "bbox": [103.1, 172.9, 1177.1, 193.9]}, {"text": "processes and developing and monitoring trading limits.  The Trading Risk Management group is separate from the transacting", "bbox": [103.1, 195.4, 1177.1, 216.4]}, {"text": "group.  For markets where independent third-party data is readily available, validation is conducted daily by directly reviewing this", "bbox": [103.1, 217.9, 1177.1, 238.9]}, {"text": "market data against inputs utilized by the transacting group, and indirectly by critically reviewing daily risk reports.  For markets", "bbox": [103.1, 240.4, 1177.1, 261.4]}, {"text": "where independent third-party data is not readily available, additional analytical reviews are performed on at least a quarterly", "bbox": [103.1, 262.9, 1177.1, 283.9]}, {"text": "basis.  These analytical reviews are designed to ensure that all price and volatility curves used for fair valuing transactions are", "bbox": [103.1, 285.4, 1177.1, 306.4]}, {"text": "adequately validated each quarter, and are reviewed and approved by the Trading Risk Management group.  In addition, other", "bbox": [103.1, 307.9, 1177.1, 328.9]}, {"text": "valuation assumptions such as implied correlations and customer migration rates are reviewed and approved by the Trading Risk", "bbox": [103.1, 330.4, 1177.1, 351.4]}, {"text": "Management group on a periodic basis.  Newly created models used in the valuation process are also subject to testing and approval", "bbox": [103.1, 352.9, 1177.1, 373.9]}, {"text": "by the Trading Risk Management group prior to use and established models are reviewed annually, or more often as needed, by", "bbox": [103.1, 375.4, 1177.1, 396.4]}, {"text": "the Trading Risk Management group.", "bbox": [103.1, 397.9, 411.6, 418.9]}, {"text": "On a monthly basis, the Exposure Management Committee (EMC), which is comprised of certain members of senior management,", "bbox": [103.1, 442.9, 1177.1, 463.9]}, {"text": "meets with representatives from the Trading Risk Management group and the transacting group to discuss NEE's and FPL's energy", "bbox": [103.1, 465.4, 1177.1, 486.4]}, {"text": "risk profile and operations, to review risk reports and to discuss fair value issues as necessary.  The EMC develops guidelines", "bbox": [103.1, 487.9, 1177.1, 508.9]}, {"text": "required for an appropriate risk management control infrastructure, which includes implementation and monitoring of compliance", "bbox": [103.1, 510.4, 1177.1, 531.4]}, {"text": "with Trading Risk Management policy.  The EMC executes its risk management responsibilities through direct oversight and", "bbox": [103.1, 532.9, 1177.1, 553.9]}, {"text": "delegation of its responsibilities to the Trading Risk Management group, as well as to other corporate and business unit personnel.", "bbox": [103.1, 555.4, 1171.9, 576.4]}, {"text": "The significant unobservable inputs used in the valuation of NEE's commodity contracts categorized as Level 3 of the fair value", "bbox": [103.1, 600.4, 1177.1, 621.4]}, {"text": "hierarchy at December 31, 2013 are as follows:", "bbox": [103.1, 622.9, 496.0, 643.9]}, {"text": "Transaction Type", "bbox": [214.4, 703.3, 335.1, 720.7]}, {"text